data.author: Kant
data.message: Hark! What words shall fill this space, where presently the noble script shall grace this page? Shall I speak of love and war, of hope and grief, of life and death? Nay, for it is not yet time. Let us instead ponder the great mysteries of the world, the questions that vex us so, that keep us up at night, and that drive us to seek knowledge and truth.Perchance we might consider the nature of the stars, and how they twinkle in the night sky, or the majesty of the sun, as it rises each day to warm and nourish our souls. Or we might speak of the endless sea, and the mysteries that lie hidden in its depths, or the forests, with their tangled paths and ancient trees. Let us take a moment to reflect upon the beauty of life, and the wonder that surrounds us every day. For though we may not always see it, there is magic in this world, and it is our privilege to partake of it. So let us be grateful for this moment, and for all the moments that are yet to come.

data.author: Venky
data.message: If I woke up one day and didn't see you in my pants; Is this life worth living? If I drooled on my nose, gravity exposed; Is life worth living? Oh! gracious C-Men save us!

data.author: Venky
data.message: 10 days past; This journey began... Nor monkey nor I, failure hence; Thou kicks't me, brings't me down! Oh fool! Never think I won't rebound.

data.author: Venky
data.message: Upon this journey embark once again, some spy looks disgust. In felony, no crime. This twerkmonster booty sublime, snooty patootie grimes. He jingle my bell, fancy knell, sunflower smell, DO NOT YELL!

data.author: Kant
data.message: Oh woe is me, forsooth, I am sorely disappointed in myself! Nay, truly, is it so difficult for me to restrain from self-pleasure for but a mere ten days? Ten days, I pray! What manner of wretch have I become, that I must needs improve myself and elevate my conduct! I shall not last until my thirtieth year if I persist in such licentious ways. Thus do I pen this reminder to myself: if I succeed in abstaining from the carnal embrace of mine own loins for yet another ten days, commencing on the tenth day of this month of March in the year of our Lord two thousand and twenty-three, then one hundred or even one thousand days shall pose no challenge to me!
